      "seed": 1534274144,
      "version": 149,
      "versionNonce": 283953056,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771515014269,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. reqs\n2. core entities\n3. APIs\n4. high level design\n5. deep dives",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. reqs\n2. core entities\n3. APIs\n4. high level design\n5. deep dives",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "L46P1yRaGVgPZOm87TZyN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 74.98495321382057,
      "y": 668.0862828562296,
      "width": 981.67919921875,
      "height": 675,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0d",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 909170272,
      "version": 1053,
      "versionNonce": 1457324640,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771515014269,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "requirements\n\nfunc:\n- users need to input start & end -> get an estimation fare\n- user should be able ot request a ride based on estimate\n- driver should be able to accept/deny a req & navigate to pick up/ dropoff\n\n----OOS----\n- multiple car types\n- ratings system, chat, schedule a ride in advance etc.\n\n\nnon func:\n- latency in matching (~1min to match user with driver)\n- CP vs AP? consistency of matching => 1 ride to driver is 1-1 not multiple drivers to 1 [consistency]\n- highly available outside of mathing => avail >> consistency\n- handle high throughput => alot of requests >100k within a given region\n\n---OOS----\n- GDPR user privacy\n- resilience & handling system failures\n- monitoring, logging, alerting\n- CI/CD pipeline\n\nalot of candidates do back of the env estimations for now but,\nits my preference to forgo them for now, and that instead i do estimations during my high lvl design\nif there is some caclulations that i need to do that will influence my design",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "requirements\n\nfunc:\n- users need to input start & end -> get an estimation fare\n- user should be able ot request a ride based on estimate\n- driver should be able to accept/deny a req & navigate to pick up/ dropoff\n\n----OOS----\n- multiple car types\n- ratings system, chat, schedule a ride in advance etc.\n\n\nnon func:\n- latency in matching (~1min to match user with driver)\n- CP vs AP? consistency of matching => 1 ride to driver is 1-1 not multiple drivers to 1 [consistency]\n- highly available outside of mathing => avail >> consistency\n- handle high throughput => alot of requests >100k within a given region\n\n---OOS----\n- GDPR user privacy\n- resilience & handling system failures\n- monitoring, logging, alerting\n- CI/CD pipeline\n\nalot of candidates do back of the env estimations for now but,\nits my preference to forgo them for now, and that instead i do estimations during my high lvl design\nif there is some caclulations that i need to do that will influence my design",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "dyV5QhoUNfkjdR13Qc91j",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -1087.1229593400394,
      "y": 1345.2251579689882,
      "width": 474.8197326660156,
      "height": 125,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0f",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1441406560,
      "version": 359,
