      "updated": 1771515014270,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Deep dive 2: Consistency of matching",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Deep dive 2: Consistency of matching",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Pk1gYBwFHkzlZ0-zlRuX8",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 977.0062430745016,
      "y": 2950.365146267118,
      "width": 1278.5791015625,
      "height": 1150,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b1b",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 193623968,
      "version": 1853,
      "versionNonce": 1985875552,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771515204195,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. we cant send more than 1 req at a time for a given ride\n2. we dont send any driver more than 1 req at a time\n\nfor 1.\n-  we're gna get a list of drivers (from getDriversLocation())\n- logic within ride matching service\n    while we dont have a matching driver send another driver a req (wait 10s)\n- a single that needs matching is only being handled by 1 single instance of the matching service\n\nfor 2,\n- we have multiple ride matching services\n- closest driver is the same for alot of people => (getDriversLocation() returns same drivers to multiple matching service instance)\n    - 1 way is to set status => req sent to this driver\n    - where the DB check & set is atomic\n    - (similar to no double booking in ticket master)\n\nissue:\n- only want to send the request for a certain period of time (driver has a certain period of time to accept it)\n- this status is stuck now coz status not updated\n    => introduce cron job?? run every n secs\n    => look for reqSentStatus drivers and see if it has been 10s\n    => introduces a delta n issue (cron job only runs once a min, whereas driver should be available after 5 secs)\n    => not optimal\n\n*think, how do we keep shared state that will expire?\n\nsoln:\n- distributed lock\n- have redis instance\n    => SET driverId True Expire 5s\n\nSET lock_key unique_value NX PX 30000\n\nlock_key = driverId\nunique_value = true?\nNX => set if not true\nPX 5_000\n*this lookup is really quick => is a hashmap\n\nif the driver doesnt respond, the lock will expire\nthen another person can go in to get the next driver\n*this distributed lock gives us a consistent global view of which drivers are available to send requests to\n\nPLUS\n- use redis sorted sets\n- iterate over available drivers stored on ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. we cant send more than 1 req at a time for a given ride\n2. we dont send any driver more than 1 req at a time\n\nfor 1.\n-  we're gna get a list of drivers (from getDriversLocation())\n- logic within ride matching service\n    while we dont have a matching driver send another driver a req (wait 10s)\n- a single that needs matching is only being handled by 1 single instance of the matching service\n\nfor 2,\n- we have multiple ride matching services\n- closest driver is the same for alot of people => (getDriversLocation() returns same drivers to multiple matching service instance)\n    - 1 way is to set status => req sent to this driver\n    - where the DB check & set is atomic\n    - (similar to no double booking in ticket master)\n\nissue:\n- only want to send the request for a certain period of time (driver has a certain period of time to accept it)\n- this status is stuck now coz status not updated\n    => introduce cron job?? run every n secs\n    => look for reqSentStatus drivers and see if it has been 10s\n    => introduces a delta n issue (cron job only runs once a min, whereas driver should be available after 5 secs)\n    => not optimal\n\n*think, how do we keep shared state that will expire?\n\nsoln:\n- distributed lock\n- have redis instance\n    => SET driverId True Expire 5s\n\nSET lock_key unique_value NX PX 30000\n\nlock_key = driverId\nunique_value = true?\nNX => set if not true\nPX 5_000\n*this lookup is really quick => is a hashmap\n\nif the driver doesnt respond, the lock will expire\nthen another person can go in to get the next driver\n*this distributed lock gives us a consistent global view of which drivers are available to send requests to\n\nPLUS\n- use redis sorted sets\n- iterate over available drivers stored on ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
